{
  "texts": [
    "Our chatbot was able to service approximately 1000 requests per day at its peak usage but ran on a small commodity desktop computer.Finally, RAG systems are easy to extend.",
    "Since RAG fundamentally relies on database technology to organize documents, adding a new course is as simple as creating and linking in a new database with the appropriate documents.",
    "This way, it is possible to rapidly create several databases with course-aligned instructions that may contradict each other, as in our beginner-to-advanced programming example above, and simply redirect the queries to the appropriate database when a query comes in for a given course.",
    "Understanding the RAG architectureA RAG system consists of three major pieces: a document parser, an embedding model, and a database.The document parser is a piece of middleware whose job it is to break down a document into smaller chunks of text.",
    "Parsing a complex document, such as one that has many images and tables, is a difficult task that is beyond the scope of this paper."
  ]
}